==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Singletree
<hw>Sin"gle*tree`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Swingletree</er>.]</ety> <def>The pivoted or swinging bar to which
the traces of a harnessed horse are fixed; a whiffletree.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ When two horses draw abreast, a <xex>singletree</xex> is
fixed at each end of another crosspiece, called the
<xex>doubletree</xex>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Singly</ent>⟦br⟧
